President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Brian Callanan of New Jersey as the General Counsel for the Department of the Treasury. Callanan has extensive legal experience in both the public and private sectors, including serving as the Deputy General Counsel for the Department of the Treasury and as the Acting General Counsel. He has also worked in private practice focusing on appellate and regulatory litigation and government investigations. Callanan has held senior positions in the United States Senate and currently serves as a Government member of the Administrative Conference of the United States.

Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to nominate Brent James McIntosh of Michigan as the Under Secretary of the Treasury for International Affairs. McIntosh is currently the General Counsel for the Department of the Treasury and leads the Treasury Legal Division. He has previously served in the White House as Associate Counsel to the President and Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Staff Secretary. McIntosh has also worked in the Department of Justice's Office of Legal Policy and clerked for judges in the United States Court of Appeals.

Lastly, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Ray W. Washburne of Texas as a Member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board.